: Call the service with a real meeting transcript, capture the LLM's summary output, evaluate the summary for coherence, accuracy, and key point capture using human judgment or automated metrics.\n- **plan_consistent**: true (Agentic level testing with real LLM is needed to catch real failures in summary quality)\n\n**Behavior 3: LLM extracts action items**\n\n- **description**: The LLM extracts action items from the meeting transcript and attributes them to specific attendees\n\n.\n- **minimum_level**: Agentic\n- **justification**: The failure is about the LLM's ability to extract and attribute action items, which requires testing the LLM's reasoning and output quality. Mocking the LLM would hide real failures in action item extraction. Testing with a real LLM is necessary to verify that action items are correctly extracted and attributed.\n- **test_description**: Call the service with a real meeting transcript containing clear task assignments, capture the LLM's action item output, verify that every attendee who was assigned a task appears in the action items list with at least one item attributed to them.\n- **plan_consistent**: true (Agentic level testing with real LLM is needed to catch real failures in action item extraction)\n\n**Behavior 4: Long audio handling with segmentation**\n\n- **description**: When the audio file is longer than 60 minutes, the service splits it into segments and processes them sequentially, merging the results into a single coherent summary.\n- **minimum_level**: Integration\n- **justification**: The failure could occur at the boundary between the service and the STT API. The service needs to correctly split the audio, send segments to the STT API, and handle the responses. Testing at Unit level would miss real API failures. Testing at System level would be overkill for a service-level orchestration issue. Integration testing with a real STT API is necessary to verify that the service correctly coordinates with the API for segment processing.\n- **test_description**: Upload a 90-minute meeting recording to the service, verify that the service splits it into segments, calls the STT API for each segment independently, and merges the transcripts into a single coherent summary without gaps or contradictions.\n- **plan_consistent**: true (Integration level testing with real STT API is needed to catch real failures in segment handling)\n\n**Behavior 5: Service handles API errors gracefully**\n\n- **description**: When the STT API returns an error, the service handles it gracefully and returns a meaningful error message to the user.\n- **minimum_level**: Integration\n- **justification**: The failure is about how the service handles errors from the STT API, which requires testing the service's error handling logic with a real API. Mocking the API would hide real failures in error handling. Testing with a real STT API (or a test endpoint that simulates errors) is necessary to verify that the service handles API errors gracefully.\n- **test_description**: Call the service with an audio file and simulate an STT API error (e.g., timeout, invalid response), verify that the service catches the error and returns a meaningful error message to the user without crashing.\n- **plan_consistent**: true (Integration level testing with real STT API error scenarios is needed to catch real failures in error handling)","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12885,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12885},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8728dcf8-130d-4f49-90ec-afc850c77ad8","uuid":"d938ff4e-b06c-4c15-a363-f6e182fdecb6"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_011soFjmJXSUkggPvvoVbud8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Looking at this meeting transcription service, I need to identify where real failures would occur and what level of test infrastructure would catch them.\n\nLet me work through each behavior systematically:\n\n**Behavior 1 (Speaker labels)**: The failure boundary is at the **real STT API**. A mock STT that returns labels would hide the real failure—that the actual API doesn't return labels or returns them in an unexpected format. Testing requires calling the real API to verify labels are both returned and preserved. → **System**\n\n**Behavior 2 (Action items per attendee)**: This depends on **LLM judgment**. The real failure is that the LLM might fail to extract assignments, misattribute them, or omit some attendees. Mocking the LLM would always make it pass. → **Agentic**\n\n**Behavior 3 (Decisions in correct section)**: Similarly, this is **LLM judgment**. The real failure is that the model embeds decisions in the narrative instead of the decisions section. A mock LLM would hide this. → **Agentic**\n\n**Behavior 4 (Long audio segmentation & merge)**: This involves **multiple real API steps**:\n- Real STT API calls for each segment (System failure: API can't handle segmented audio)\n- Real LLM call to merge segment transcripts coherently (Agentic failure: LLM can't produce coherent merged output)\n- Orchestration tying them together (Workflow failure: pipeline breaks)\n\nTesting at System (real STT, mocked LLM) would miss LLM merging failures. Testing at Agentic (real LLM, mocked STT) would miss STT integration issues. Only **Workflow** tests the full pipeline end-to-end. → **Workflow**\n\n**Behavior 5 (Full pipeline without intervention)**: The pipeline involves file I/O (System), STT API (System), LLM API (Agentic), and orchestration. Real failures include API timeouts, unexpected response formats, orchestration bugs, and LLM quality issues that cause stalls. Only **Workflow** level testing catches all of these. → **Workflow**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12885,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12885},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8728dcf8-130d-4f49-90ec-afc850c77ad8","uuid":"0ed86b33-fd6c-4511-a153-fe8838251ecb"}
